    <item>
      <title>Quotes of Detachment</title>
      <link>https://dreambooker.site/2018/09/05/Quotes-of-Detachment/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 05 Sep 2018 14:45:24 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://dreambooker.site/2018/09/05/Quotes-of-Detachment/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Albert Camus&lt;/strong&gt;: And never have I felt so deeply at one and the same time so detached from myself and so present in the world.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;quotes&#34;&gt;Quotes:&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;H: Most of the teachers here, at one point &amp;hellip; they believed &amp;hellip; that they could make a difference. You know, I know how important it is to have guidance and to have someone help understand the complexities of the world that we live in. I didn&amp;rsquo;t really have that growing up.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;H: I&amp;rsquo;m money. I change hands like a dollar bill that&amp;rsquo;s been robbed by a lamp when a genie appeared and cried loudly, with volume. But the tears were all for myself. And that&amp;rsquo;s where it all went wrong.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
